  "notes": "Per-hole par, stroke index (single men's allocation printed on the card) and distances come from the club's official Libro de Campo/Strokesaver PDF (tarjeta de recorrido page plus 18 individual hole pages), cross-checked hole-by-hole against 18Birdies (identical par, SI and white-tee meters). Course rating (Vc) and slope (Vs) per tee/gender are from the current RFEG club page. Discrepancies: (1) RFEG's current rated lengths are shorter than the club card sums - Blancas 6256 m, Amarillas 5963 m, Azules 5396 m, Rojas 5229 m vs card 6367/6096/5483/5329 - indicating a re-measurement/re-rating after the 2022 strokesaver was printed; per-hole breakdowns for the RFEG lengths are not published, so the club-card per-hole meters are reported and each tee's totalMeters matches its per-hole sum. (2) Red hole 3 prints ambiguously as 285 on the summary card, but the front-nine total (2611) and the hole page both confirm 282. (3) Azules per-hole distances are not on the printed summary card; they were compiled from the 18 hole pages of the same official PDF. Older ratings on the strokesaver (yellow slope 137) and golfshake (yellow 72/138, red 74/132) are superseded by the RFEG values. Course: 18 holes, par 72, designer Ramon Espinosa."
